Monday August 19th 2013 9:35 am -04:00,The rules for executing a return statement:    Evaluate the expression. This produces a memory address.    Pass back that memory address to the caller. Exit the function.Notice that last part of step 2: Exit the function. As part of the execution of the first return statement the function exits so the second return statement is not reached and isnt executed., Resolved,5
